comments.body: Need some clarification on how the desired outcome for maps relate to the display and behavior of non-map Multi-volume works.
@tpendragon @eliotjordan  - am I understanding correctly that multi-volume works should have multiple viewers, but "ScannedMap" (per graphql) resources should have a single viewer?

@maxkadel For documentation, https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/pull/3286 is the PR where I broke this.

I think it's this:

If I get back two resources and one of them is in the `member_ids` of another, don't display the child.

There's never a case where we want to display the MVW manifest -and- the volume manifest on the same page.

We used to filter it out so if there was a MVW and a Volume then it'd only display MVWs, but finding if something is a MVW is pretty expensive and that isn't a precise enough calculation anyways.

@tpendragon That PR is part of why I'm confused. 

### Scenario 1 - 1 physical object with 2 Figgy records, one for regular imaging, one for multi-spectral imaging
So, https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9950403683506421 should still have 2 viewers after whatever changes I make, since there is 
* 1 physical object with a recto and verso
* 1 catalog record for that object
* 2 Figgy objects
  * 1 Figgy object is a simple object (not nested) with 2 images, one of the recto and one of the verso, which translates to one iiif viewer (see https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/bbc6f6c4-3b92-4ae9-8461-1a14c113af8c)
    * This is represented in the iiif manifest as `@type: "sc:Manifest"`
  * 1 Figgy object is a complex object with two nested "members" (see https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/54b399c7-f28c-46f6-a7b4-c835a60516c4)
    * Each "member" is a set of multi-spectral images
    * Both members are represented in a single iiif manifest as `@type: "sc:Collection"`, resulting in a single viewer

### Scenario 2 - 1 map in 6 sheets and 1 Figgy record
https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9968107933506421 - Should have a single viewer after whatever changes I make
* 1 conceptual object in six pieces (1 map, 6 sheets)
* 1 catalog record
* 1 Figgy object
  * Complex object with 7 nested "Child Scanned Maps" (one for each sheet, plus one of all of the sheets digitally stitched together)
  * Each manifest that Orangelight fetches has `@type: "sc:Manifest"`. The one that has all of the images has multiple canvases under Sequences: Canvases, whereas the single images on have on canvas.

So, could we say that the number of viewers should match the number of (parent?) Figgy objects?
